What is the clinical story? Myxoma and PFE can look very similar on 2D, although the size and appearance is suggestive of PFE here. There have been case reports with mixed features histologically.

Replying to 
@purviparwani
 @mariovar55
  and 14 others
Morphology most consistent w/ #papillaryfibroblastoma (fronds attached to pedicle); LAA rare location for PFE, 90% on leaflets; risk for thromboembolism. Less likely pedunculated myxoma (also rare in LAA, appearance here atypical for myxoma). Unlikely thrombus, N LA contractility
